inlineContent.text: protocol is a convenience protocol that adopts all of the protocols used to handle ride sharing-related intents. When your app adopts all of the protocols associated with ride sharing, you can adopt this one protocol instead of adopting the
An object that adopts this protocol must be able to respond to the following intents:
, a request to view the available vehicles and prices.
, a request to book a ride.
, a request to get the status of a previously booked ride.
, a request to cancel the currently active ride.
, a request to record feedback for the just-completed ride.

Your handler object must be prepared to resolve any parameters associated with these intents and to confirm and handle the requests. When confirming and handling a request, you provide the response object that matches the specified intent.
